class.name: ExpCurve
class.descr: An enum that represents the different types of EXP curves in the game.

mem.name: SLOW
mem.descr: Exp is gained slowly.

mem.name: MEDIUM_SLOW
mem.descr: Exp is gained slightly faster than slow.

mem.name: MEDIUM_FAST
mem.descr: Exp is gained pretty fast.

mem.name: FAST
mem.descr: Exp is gained fast.

mem.name: ERRATIC
mem.descr: The ExpCurve is erratic.

mem.name: FLUCTUATING
mem.descr: The ExpCurve is fluctuating.

class.name: Type
class.descr: An enum that represent every different pokemon/move Type in the game.

class.name: Pokemon
class.descr: A class that represents a Pokemon.

mem.name: name
mem.descr: The name of the Pokemon. In some cases, this variable will not be printable because it contains illegal characters (like male/female signs). To prevent an exception, pass it through the toStr function.

mem.name: number
mem.descr: The Species number of the Pokemon. Corresponds to the values in the Species class.

mem.name: baseForme
mem.descr: The base forme of this Pokemon, or None when this is already the base forme. Different formes might have unexpected Species numbers because they are different in each generation, so when formes are included this variable can be used to get the correct Species number. You can also use the Pokemon.getBaseNumber method for this purpose.

mem.name: formeNumber
mem.descr: The number of the forme of this Pokemon. This is for Pokemon with multiple alternate formes like deoxys and rotom.

mem.name: primaryType
mem.descr: The primary Type of this Pokemon.

mem.name: secondaryType
mem.descr: The secondary Type of this Pokemon, or None if it only has one Type.

mem.name: hp
mem.descr: The HP base stat of this Pokemon.

mem.name: attack
mem.descr: The Attack base stat of this Pokemon.

mem.name: defense
mem.descr: The Defense base stat of this Pokemon.

mem.name: spatk
mem.descr: The Special Attack base stat of this Pokemon.

mem.name: spdef
mem.descr: The Special Defense base stat of this Pokemon.

mem.name: speed
mem.descr: The Speed base stat of this Pokemon.

mem.name: special
mem.descr: The Special (Gen 1 only) base stat of this Pokemon.

mem.name: ability1
mem.descr: The first Ability slot of this Pokemon. The total number of abilities can be found in ROM.maxAbilities.

mem.name: ability2
mem.descr: The second Ability slot of this Pokemon. The total number of abilities can be found in ROM.maxAbilities.

mem.name: ability3
mem.descr: The third Ability slot of this Pokemon. The total number of abilities can be found in ROM.maxAbilities.

mem.name: catchRate
mem.descr: The catch rate of this Pokemon.

mem.name: expYield
mem.descr: The Exp yield of this Pokemon.

mem.name: guaranteedHeldItem
mem.descr: The guaranteed held Item of this Pokemon when caught in the wild. This Item will always be held if it isn't Items.none.

mem.name: commonHeldItem
mem.descr: The common held Item of this Pokemon when caught in the wild. This Item will often be held if it isn't Items.none.

mem.name: rareHeldItem
mem.descr: The rare held Item of this Pokemon when caught in the wild. This Item will rarely be held if it isn't Items.none.

mem.name: darkGrassHeldItem
mem.descr: The dark grass held Item of this Pokemon when caught in the wild. This Item can be held by Pokemon caught in the dark grass (in games that feature dark grass) if it isn't Items.none.

mem.name: genderRatio
mem.descr: The gender ratio of this Pokemon.

mem.name: growthCurve
mem.descr: The ExpCurve that is used by this Pokemon.

mem.name: evolutionsFrom
mem.descr: A Java list of Evolution objects representing every Evolution where this Pokemon is the result. Can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: evolutionsTo
mem.descr: A Java list of Evolution objects representing every Evolution where this Pokemon is the original. Can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: megaEvolutionsFrom
mem.descr: A Java list of MegaEvolution objects representing every MegaEvolution where this Pokemon is the original.

mem.name: megaEvolutionsTo
mem.descr: A Java list of MegaEvolution objects representing every MegaEvolution where this Pokemon is the original.

meth.name: bst
meth.descr: Gets the base stat total (BST) of this Pokemon.

return.descr: The base stat total of this Pokemon.

meth.name: bstForPowerLevels
meth.descr: Gets a modified version of the base stat total (BST) of this Pokemon that takes some edge cases into account to provide a more accurate result. This is used by similarStrength.

return.descr: The modified base stat total of this Pokemon.

meth.name: getAttackSpecialAttackRatio
meth.descr: Gets the [0-1] ratio of attack vs. special attack. For example: if this is 0.4 that means that the attack stat is 40% of (attack + special attack).

return.descr: The attack to special attack ratio of this Pokemon.

meth.name: getBaseNumber
meth.descr: Gets the Species number of the base forme of this Pokemon.

return.descr: The Species number of the base forme of this Pokemon.

meth.name: fullName
meth.descr: Gets the full name of this Pokemon, including a forme suffix if it is a forme of another Pokemon. This value may not be printable in some cases where it includes special characters (like male/female signs). To prevent exceptions you can pass this value through the toStr function.

return.descr: Gets the full name of this Pokemon, including a forme suffix if it is a forme of another Pokemon.

meth.name: isLegendary
meth.descr: Checks if this Pokemon is considered a legendary.

return.descr: True if this Pokemon is considered a legendary.

meth.name: isStrongLegendary
meth.descr: Checks if this Pokemon is considered a 'strong' legendary. This includes the main-game legendaries like mewtwo, kyogre, groudon, reshiram, zekrom, etc.

return.descr: True if this Pokemon is considered a 'strong' legendary.

class.name: TrainerPokemon
class.descr: A class that represents a Pokemon owned by a Trainer.

mem.name: pokemon
mem.descr: The actual Pokemon.

mem.name: level
mem.descr: The level of the TrainerPokemon

mem.name: heldItem
mem.descr: The held Item of the TrainerPokemon. You can get Items by variable name in the Items class and you can convert them to strings with the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to their Item indices again using the index function.

mem.name: hasMegaStone
mem.descr: True if this TrainerPokemon should hold a mega stone.

mem.name: hasZCrystal
mem.descr: True if this TrainerPokemon should hold a z-crystal.

mem.name: abilitySlot
mem.descr: The Ability slot used by this TrainerPokemon.

mem.name: forme
mem.descr: The forme of this TrainerPokemon.

mem.name: nature
mem.descr: The nature of this TrainerPokemon.

mem.name: moves
mem.descr: Array of integers representing the Moves of this TrainerPokemon. You can access Moves by variable name in the Moves class and convert them to strings using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to their Move indices again using the index function.

mem.name: resetMoves
mem.descr: True when the moves of the TrainerPokemon have been modified so the randomizer knows to update them.

mem.name: hpEVs
mem.descr: The EVs (effort values) this TrainerPokemon has in HP. This only works in games where TrainerPokemon can have EVs (like sun/moon).

mem.name: atkEVs
mem.descr: The EVs (effort values) this TrainerPokemon has in Attack. This only works in games where TrainerPokemon can have EVs (like sun/moon).

mem.name: defEVs
mem.descr: The EVs (effort values) this TrainerPokemon has in Defense. This only works in games where TrainerPokemon can have EVs (like sun/moon).

mem.name: spatkEVs
mem.descr: The EVs (effort values) this TrainerPokemon has in Special Attack. This only works in games where TrainerPokemon can have EVs (like sun/moon).

mem.name: spdefEVs
mem.descr: The EVs (effort values) this TrainerPokemon has in Special Defense. This only works in games where TrainerPokemon can have EVs (like sun/moon).

mem.name: speedEVs
mem.descr: The EVs (effort values) this TrainerPokemon has in Speed. This only works in games where TrainerPokemon can have EVs (like sun/moon).

mem.name: IVs
mem.descr: The IVs of this TrainerPokemon, packed in a single integer.

meth.name: canMegaEvolve
meth.descr: Checks if this TrainerPokemon can mega-evolve. (e.g. it has a mega-evolution and holds a mega-stone)

return.descr: True if this TrainerPokemon can mega-evolve

class.name: Move
class.descr: A class that represents a Move in the game and includes more information that just a Move index (e.g. Type, Move.StatChange, power, pp, MoveCategory, etc.).

mem.name: name
mem.descr: The name of the Move.

mem.name: number
mem.descr: The index of the Move. This corresponds to the indices found in the Moves class and can also be converted to a string of the Move name with the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to their Move indices again using the index function.

mem.name: power
mem.descr: The power of the Move.

mem.name: pp
mem.descr: The Power Points (PP) of the Move. This is the number of times the Move can be used without healing.

mem.name: hitratio
mem.descr: The [0-100] percent chance that the move will hit.

mem.name: type
mem.descr: The Type of the Move.

mem.name: category
mem.descr: The MoveCategory of this Move. (e.g. physical/special/status)

mem.name: statChangeMoveType
mem.descr: The type of stat change that this Move causes.

mem.name: statChanges
mem.descr: Array of StatChange objects representing every Move.StatChange this Move causes.

mem.name: statusMoveType
mem.descr: The StatusMoveType of this Move. Used to differentiate between status moves that do damage and those that do not.

mem.name: statusType
mem.descr: The type of status condition this Move causes.

mem.name: criticalChance
mem.descr: The type of chance this Move has to land a critical hit.

mem.name: statusPercentChance
mem.descr: The [0-100] percent chance of causing the status condition in the StatusType member of this Move (if any).

mem.name: flinchPercentChance
mem.descr: The [0-100] percent chance of this Move causing the opponent to flinch.

mem.name: recoilPercent
mem.descr: The [0-100] percent of recoil damage taken when this Move is used.

mem.name: absorbPercent
mem.descr: The [0-100] percent of HP healed when this Move is used.

mem.name: priority
mem.descr: The priority of this Move.

mem.name: makesContact
mem.descr: True if this Move is considered to make contact. Used for Abilities like rough skin.

mem.name: isChargeMove
mem.descr: True if this Move is considered a charge Move. This means it takes an extra turn of idleness before the Move actually fires the next turn (e.g. solar beam).

mem.name: isRechargeMove
mem.descr: True if this Move is considered a recharge Move. This means it takes an extra turn of idleness after the Move fired (e.g. roar of time).

mem.name: isPunchMove
mem.descr: True if this Move is considered a punch Move (e.g. fire punch, thunder punch, etc.). This is used by Abilities like iron fist.

mem.name: isSoundMove
mem.descr: True if this Move is considered a sound Move (e.g. chatter, supersonic, etc.). This is used by Abilities like soundproof.

mem.name: isTrapMove
mem.descr: True if this Move is considered a trap Move. These are moves that trap the Pokemon in battle, preventing the player from switching and running (e.g. mean look, wrap, etc.).

meth.name: hasSpecificStatChange
meth.descr: Checks if the move causes a specific stat change.

arg.name: type
arg.descr: The affected stat.

arg.name: isPositive
arg.descr: True if the change should be positive (e.g. raise attack).

return.descr: True if the move causes a specific stat change.

meth.name: hasBeneficialStatChange
meth.descr: Checks if the move causes any positive stat change (e.g. raise attack).

return.descr: True if the move causes any positive stat change.

meth.name: isGoodDamaging
meth.descr: Checks if the move is considered a 'good damaging move'. This is used by 'force % good damaging moves' options.

return.descr: True if the move is considered a 'good damaging move'.

class.name: MoveCategory
class.descr: An enum that represents the different types of Moves (physical/special/status).

mem.name: PHYSICAL
mem.descr: The Move is physical and (usually) uses the Attack stat.

mem.name: SPECIAL
mem.descr: The Move is special and (usually) uses the Special Attack stat.

mem.name: STATUS
mem.descr: This is a status Move, it isn't an attack.

class.name: CriticalChance
class.descr: An enum that represents the different types of critical hit chances for any given Move.

mem.name: NONE
mem.descr: No chance for a critical hit. (Phased out in generation 5)

mem.name: NORMAL
mem.descr: The usual chance for a critical hit.

mem.name: INCREASED
mem.descr: A higher chance for a critical hit.

mem.name: GUARANTEED
mem.descr: This Move will always be a critical hit.

class.name: Encounter

mem.name: pokemon
mem.descr: The actual Pokemon that will appear.

mem.name: level
mem.descr: The base level the Pokemon can be.

mem.name: maxLevel
mem.descr: The highest level the Pokemon can be.

mem.name: formeNumber

class.name: Moves

class.descr: A class containing static constants for all the Pokemon Species indices in any ROM.

class.descr: A class containing static constants that are relevant to any ROM.

mem.name: normalMultihitMoves
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all multihit Moves like bullet seed and rock blast. You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: doubleHitMoves
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all doublehit Moves like double kick. You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: varyingPowerZMoves
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Z-Moves with varying power. You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: fixedPowerZMoves
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Z-Moves with fixed power. You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: zMoves
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Z-Moves. You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: xItems
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all X-Items. You can get Item indices by variable name using the Items class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Item index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: battleTrappingAbilities
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all trapping Abilities (Abilities that make it impossible for the opponent to switch or run away) like arena trap. You can get Ability indices by variable name using the Abilities class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Ability index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: negativeAbilities
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Abilities that have a negative effect on the user, like truant or slow start. You can get Ability indices by variable name using the Abilities class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Ability index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: badAbilities
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Abilities marked as 'bad' like forewarn. These are what is excluded when using the 'ban bad Abilities' option. You can get Ability indices by variable name using the Abilities class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Ability index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: doubleBattleAbilities
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Abilities that only affect double battles like friend guard. You can get Ability indices by variable name using the Abilities class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Ability index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: duplicateAbilities
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Abilities that have functional duplicates like vital spirit. These are excluded when using the 'combine duplicate abilities' option. You can get Ability indices by variable name using the Abilities class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Ability index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: noPowerNonStatusMoves
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Moves that have no specific Move power and don't inflict status effects, like dragon rage and counter. You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: doubleBattleMoves
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Moves that only affect double battles like heling hand and follow me. You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: uselessMoves
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all useless Moves like splash and teleport. It also includes reflectType because the AI doesn't know how to use it. You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

mem.name: requiresOtherMove
mem.descr: A Java list of integers representing all Moves that require other Moves to take effect like nightmare (requires sleep) and swallow (requires stockpile). You can get Move indices by variable name using the Moves class. You can also convert them to strings containing their name using the toStr function and you can convert those strings back to the Move index using the index function. This Java list can be converted to a python sequence using the seq function.

meth.name: getAllies

func.name: selectStarter
func.descr:
Enabled when selecting "Scripted" under "Starter Pokemon". Gets called to select every starter pokemon individually.
Note: you can call ROM.getStarters() to get the original starters.

arg.name: pokepool
arg.descr: A sequence of pokemon objects representing all pokemon this function can choose from

arg.name: starterIndex
arg.descr: The index-number of the starter (usually 0-2, but can be higher in games where you pick starters multiple times like the gen 1 starters in X&Y).

return.descr: A Pokemon object, that exists in the given pokepool, that this starter should be replaced by.
